      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Documented peer review of model setup, boundary conditions, and load application by an independent analyst not involved in model development.",
      "rationale": "Independent peer review conducted by FDA CDRH computational modeling staff. Boundary conditions, load application, and material assignments verified against ASTM F1717 protocol. No use errors identified. Achieved level 3 due to cross-institutional review."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The continuum mechanics assumptions (linear elasticity, small deformation) must be justified relative to the operating regime; nonlinear effects must be evaluated and scoped.",
      "rationale": "Compression-bending loads remain within the elastic regime for the titanium alloy construct up to yield. Geometric nonlinearity (large displacement) is activated in the solver to capture load-path effects at higher displacements. Model form uncertainty quantified via sensitivity analysis; contribution to total uncertainty budget is 3.2%."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties (Ti-6Al-4V elastic modulus, yield strength) must be sourced from coupon testing of the same material lot used for the experimental constructs, or from peer-reviewed literature with documented uncertainty bounds.",
      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V material properties sourced from tensile coupon tests (n=6) from the same billet used to manufacture the experimental constructs. Elastic modulus 114 ± 3 GPa; yield strength 880 ± 15 MPa. UHMWPE block properties from literature (Kurtz 2009) with documented uncertainty. Input uncertainty propagated via Monte Carlo (1000 samples)."
