      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Testing must span at least two distinct load conditions or screw insertion angles to characterize model response across the relevant operating space.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed at a single ASTM F1717 standard configuration (7-degree lordotic angle, 44 mm interbody distance). Variation in test conditions is limited to the two-laboratory comparison. Achieved level 2 is below required level 3; this gap is acknowledged and accepted given that the single test condition represents the worst-case configuration per ASTM F1717 protocol."
    },
    {
