      "rationale": "Construct stiffness and yield force are the primary mechanical performance metrics cited in ASTM F1717 and FDA guidance for spinal fixation systems. Force at 40 mm displacement characterizes post-yield behavior relevant to fatigue and fracture risk. All three QoIs are directly relevant to the 510(k) submission performance comparison."
