    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed required gradation levels. One factor (Test conditions) achieved Gradation 2 against a required Gradation 3; this gap is accepted because the single ASTM F1717 configuration represents the regulatory worst-case and is consistent with FDA guidance for static compression-bending submissions. All three QoIs satisfy E/uval < 1.96. The FEA modeling framework is accepted as sufficiently credible to support the 510(k) submission for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct.",
